    <p>{`SwiftUI Views are structures that conform to the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`View`}</inlineCode>{` protocol, which requires a computed property called `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`body`}</inlineCode>{` that holds the internal layout hierarchy for the view. SwiftUI files can also contain an additional structure that declares the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`PreviewProvider`}</inlineCode>{` for that view. The preview is useful for viewing live in Xcode and is ignored at compile time.`}</p>
